;; tsukuru 作 — manufacturer-registry-seed.edn (illustrative REAL-COMPANY registry seed)
;;
;; NOT an ADR-tracked live registry, NOT a verified/onboarded factory relationship, NOT a live
;; commercial offer. This is an illustrative registry seed drawn from PUBLIC KNOWLEDGE of real,
;; publicly-documented manufacturers — company identity / home-country / illustrative industry
;; category only. It widens tsukuru's real-manufacturer coverage at the kotoba-native EDN layer
;; (companion to kotoba/seed.edn's tiny 3-entry R0 worked example, which stays a small
;; fictional/representative demo on purpose — see seed.edn's own header). The separate 465-entry
;; AT-proto catalog at wire/catalogs/manufacturer-catalog.v1.json is
;; a DIFFERENT, read-only, out-of-scope JSON data file for a different consumer (~90% synthetic
;; placeholder entries) — this file does not read from or write to it, and is not a copy of it.
;;
;; ── ID scheme (IMPORTANT — reader honesty, same spirit as kotoba/agent.cljc's screen-entity "not
;;    wired" pattern) ──
;; :factory/did values below use the placeholder pattern "factory/registry-seed/<slug>" — this is
;; DELIBERATELY NOT a did:web URI, and is DISTINCT from the live path-based factory DID scheme
;; documented in CLAUDE.md (`did:web:tsukuru.etzhayyim.com/factory/<slug>`,
;; performerType=service — see also kotoba/seed.edn's :factory/did values, which DO use that live
;; scheme for its small fictional worked example). None of the real companies below have been
;; issued a did:web identity, on-chain registration, LEI, or wallet address by tsukuru — inventing
;; one would misrepresent a real legal entity as having a registration it does not actually have.
;;
;; ── What's asserted vs. what's deliberately withheld (honesty framing, G8/G10-style) ──
;;   - :factory/display-name / :factory/country / :factory/isic / :factory/capabilities are
;;     stated only where they reflect well-documented public knowledge: a company's identity, its
;;     commonly-cited primary home/operational country, and a PLAUSIBLE illustrative ISIC rev.4
;;     section/class (NOT an authoritative customs/statistical classification — same "curated,
;;     not authoritative" caveat as kotoba/agent.cljc's HS-CLASSIFICATION-TABLE). A few dual-listed /
;;     recently-restructured / dual-domiciled multinationals carry an inline comment noting the
;;     country attribution is the commonly-cited one, not a verified legal fact.
;;   - :factory/capabilities are coarse keyword tags for capability-match token-overlap scoring
;;     (kotoba/agent.cljc handle-discover) — illustrative process/vertical tags, not a verified
;;     capability audit, certification, or capacity claim.
;;   - :factory/labor-provenance is :unknown for every entry (G8) — tsukuru holds no labor-dignity
;;     disclosure for any of these real companies; :unknown is the honest default, never guessed.
;;   - :factory/sourcing is :representative (reusing kotoba/schema.edn's existing enum value) —
;;     here specifically meaning "illustrative registry seed drawn from public knowledge, NOT a
;;     verified/onboarded factory relationship, NOT a live commercial offer" (a stronger caveat
;;     than seed.edn's own small fictional-demo use of the same tag).
;;   - :factory/fulfillment-modes, exact certifications, capacity numbers, street addresses, and
;;     contact details are DELIBERATELY OMITTED for every entry — inventing them for a real,
;;     named company would fabricate specifics tsukuru has no way to verify.
;;
;; Bridged into kotoba/agent.cljc's handle-discover/capability-match via the new pure
;; `factory-datom->state` fn (kotoba :factory/* EDN entity → the plain string-keyed shape
;; handle-discover already expects, same shape as lex/factory.edn's lexicon record) — see
;; kotoba/test_agent.cljc's test-discover-ranks-real-manufacturer-registry-slice, which replays a
;; slice of the entries below verbatim.
;;
;; ~99 entries across: general contract electronics manufacturing (EMS), semiconductor
;; foundry/equipment (incl. EUV-relevant), automotive parts, aerospace/defense, robotics/
;; automation, raw materials/metals, chemicals/advanced-materials (incl. a small, less-certain
;; slice of publicly-documented carbon-nanotube producers), logistics/3PL, packaging, and
;; agriculture/food supply — the actual spread of tsukuru's verticals, not a re-run of any single
;; source list.

